ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A must-take course for students interested in image processing/analysis. Highly recommended
I would recommend because I learned a lot of useful techniques and I think they are very helpful.
Very interesting but challenging course. Definitely a huge amount of work, lots of reading, researching, homework, and test prep time.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course is directly relevant to my research. I learned a lot from this course.

I'm doing research in MRI and it's involved with imaging techniques and signal processing which are cover in the class. So some of the knowledge i had in MRI like registration, filtering etc. were all covered in class. So It allowed me to learn in depth.
